<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Global Investment Banking group serves a diverse client base that includes corporations, financial institutions, financial sponsors, hedge funds, governments and government agencies. We have a significant presence in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and Asia Pacific, serving clients in virtually all countries.
</p>
<p class="bac">
We provide our clients with a range of services fundamental to their business, including strategic advice, financing, restructuring and risk management, as well as capital rising from both the public markets and private sources. We serve our clients through teams of professionals that bring together the full capabilities of the bank to satisfy one goal: helping our clients succeed.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
As an active team member in a focused industry or product group, associates will:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Help deliver solutions that bring to bear the full breadth of the bank&#39;s capabilities - ranging from strategic mergers and acquisitions advice, debt, equity, liability derivatives, structured products, principal investing, and private equity</li>
	<li>Help win new client business and actively participate in executing transactions</li>
	<li>Work with teams of professionals across the bank, including senior bankers within your groups, experts in other areas of the firm, and colleagues around the globe</li>
	<li>Manage junior professionals/analysts to execute deals and perform various analyses</li>
	<li>Work closely with senior clients, lawyers and representatives from other investment banks</li>
	<li>Expand your level of client interaction and responsibilities on transactions as you build your experience</li>
	<li>Discover unlimited opportunities to challenge yourself and grow professionally</li>
	<li>Build relationships, knowledge, and experience that will enable you to access a wide range of future career options and opportunities</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Education</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>One year prior to completion of MBA or other advanced degree from a top tier school</li>	
	<li>Outstanding academic achievement</li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Experience</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>A track record of superior performance in extracurricular and professional activities</li>	
	<li>Minimum 3 years relevant work experience</li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Skills and abilities </H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Strong quantitative and analytical skills</li>	
	<li>Knowledge of financial services</li>	
	<li>Capability to apply advanced oral and written communication skills to create a positive impression and professional rapport</li>	
	<li>Ability to work independently while functioning as part of a team</li>	
	<li>Appropriate language capabilities</li>
</ul>
<br>
<H3 class="bac">Personal traits</H3>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>A high degree of initiative and motivation</li>	
	<li>Strong attention to detail</li>	
	<li>Quick learner</li>	
	<li>Client focused</li>	
	<li>Results driven</li>	
	<li>Composure and confidence to juggle conflicting priorities</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Our 9 week summer program involves working on projects alongside bankers in specific industry or product groups, providing you with a unique learning opportunity and exposure to life at a leading investment bank. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
The training program includes:
</p>
<ul class="bac">	
	<li>Classroom instruction prior to assignment</li>	
	<li>Summer Senior Speaker Series, featuring presentations by top executives</li>	
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>	
	<li>A mentoring program</li>	
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>

